          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-error_icon">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-error_icon"}>
              Error icon prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>error_icon</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute is a string that specifies an icon to be displayed alongside error messages in a form field. By default, this attribute is set to <.custom_inline_code>nil</.custom_inline_code>, meaning no icon is shown unless specified. You can choose any icon from the Hero Icons library to enhance the visual feedback when an error occurs, helping users quickly identify and address form issues. This customization adds an extra layer of clarity and improves user experience by associating an icon with error states.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_12}>
            <.email_field
              id="form-example-197"
              name="form-example-197"
              value="infoo@mishka.tool"
              label="Email"
              placeholder="Mishka chelekom forms"
              color="silver"
              variant="default"
              errors={["Enter a valid email"]}
              error_icon="hero-shield-exclamation"
            />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-label-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-label-prop"}>
              Label prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>label</.custom_inline_code>
            prop is a string that defines the text displayed as the label for an input field.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_13}>
            <.email_field
              id="form-example-182"
              name="form-example-182"
              value=""
              label="Email"
              placeholder="Email"
              color="misc"
              variant="default"
            />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-description-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-description-prop"}>
              Description prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>description</.custom_inline_code>
            prop is a string that provides a small, helpful text displayed below the label. This description offers additional context or guidance for users about the input field, clarifying its purpose or instructions on what to enter.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_14}>
            <.email_field
              id="form-example-198"
              name="form-example-198"
              value=""
              label="Email"
              description="please insert your work email."
              placeholder="Email"
              color="misc"
              variant="default"
            />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-name-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-name-prop"}>
              Name prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>name</.custom_inline_code>
            prop represents the name attribute for an input field, serving as a key identifier when submitting form data. It links the input value to a specific field name in the form, allowing the backend or processing scripts to correctly handle the submitted information. The
            <.custom_inline_code>name</.custom_inline_code>
            prop is essential for form submissions, ensuring that data entered by the user is captured and processed accurately. Each input field should have a unique
            <.custom_inline_code>name</.custom_inline_code>
            to avoid conflicts and ensure the proper handling of form data.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_15}>
            <.email_field
              id="form-example-194"
              name="form-example-194"
              value=""
              label="Email"
              description="please insert your work email."
              placeholder="Email"
              variant="default"
            />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-value-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-value-prop"}>
              Value prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>value</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute represents the data or content associated with the input field. It is flexible, accepting any type of value, such as strings, numbers, or other data types. The
            <.custom_inline_code>value</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute is essential for both capturing user input and pre-populating form fields with existing data. It allows the input to hold and display a specific value, ensuring that the input's state can be managed dynamically or passed along during form submissions.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_16}>
            <.email_field
              id="form-example-196"
              name="form-example-196"
              value="1@mail.com"
              label="Email"
              description="please insert your work email."
              placeholder="Email"
              color="misc"
              variant="default"
            />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-errors-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-errors-prop"}>
              Errors prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>errors</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute is a list that holds error messages related to an input field. By default, it is an empty list, but when validation fails or other issues arise, you can populate this list with relevant error messages. These messages will be displayed to inform users of any issues with their input, providing clear feedback on how to correct the problem. The
            <.custom_inline_code>errors</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute enhances the form's user experience by ensuring that users receive immediate, understandable error notifications, helping them to complete the form accurately.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_17}>
            <.email_field
              id="form-example-179"
              name="form-example-179"
              value="1@mail.info"
              label="Email"
              description="please insert your work email."
              placeholder="Email"
              color="silver"
              variant="default"
              errors={["Invalid email"]}
            />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-start-end-section-slot">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-start-end-section-slot"}>
              start and end section slots
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>errors</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute is a list that holds error messages related to an input field. By default, it is an empty list, but when validation fails or other issues arise, you can populate this list with relevant error messages. These messages will be displayed to inform users of any issues with their input, providing clear feedback on how to correct the problem. The
            <.custom_inline_code>errors</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute enhances the form's user experience by ensuring that users receive immediate, understandable error notifications, helping them to complete the form accurately.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_18}>
            <.tel_field
              id="form-example-178"
              name="form-example-178"
              value=""
              label="Phone"
              placeholder="Enter your phone"
              variant="default"
            >
              <:start_section>
                +31
              </:start_section>
            </.tel_field>

            <.text_field
              id="form-example-75"
              name="form-example-75"
              value=""
              label="Username"
              placeholder="Enter your username"
              color="dawn"
              variant="default"
            >
              <:end_section>
                <svg
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  width="20"
                  height="20"
                  fill="none"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="1.25"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                >
                  <path d="M18 20a6 6 0 0 0-12 0" /><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="4" /><circle
                    cx="12"
                    cy="12"
                    r="10"
                  />
                </svg>
              </:end_section>
            </.text_field>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="form-form-wrapper">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-form-wrapper"}>
              Form wrapper component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>form_wrapper</.custom_inline_code>
            component in Phoenix LiveView is used to wrap form elements and manage form data. It has two key attributes that enhance its functionality. The
            <.custom_inline_code>for</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute is optional and represents the data structure that the form will bind to, allowing the form to be populated with existing data or updated dynamically. The
            <.custom_inline_code>as</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute allows you to group all form inputs under a specific server-side parameter, making it easier to handle the form data on submission. These attributes provide flexibility in how form data is structured and managed in LiveView applications.
          </.cp>
          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" elements_class="space-y-4" code={@code_19}>
            <.form_wrapper for={%{}} space="large">
              <.text_field name="name" value="" label="Full Name" size="small" />
              <.text_field name="add" value="" label="Adress" size="small" />
              <.text_field name="tel" value="" label="Phone" size="small" />
              <.text_field name="zip" value="" label="Zipcode" size="small" />
              <.email_field name="email" value="" label="Email" size="small" />

              <.native_select name="job" label="Choose your Job" size="small">
                <:option value="1">
                  Backend developer
                </:option>

                <:option value="2">
                  Front developer
                </:option>
              </.native_select>

              <.date_time_field
                size="small"
                type="datetime-local"
                name="form-example-90"
                value=""
                space="small"
                label="Start office hour"
                id="form-example-90"
              />

              <.date_time_field
                size="small"
                type="datetime-local"
                name="form-example-91"
                value=""
                space="small"
                label="Start office day"
                id="form-example-91"
              />

              <.checkbox_field name="" value="" label="Terms" color="base" />

              <.range_field name="sal" value="" label="Salary" color="base" />
            </.form_wrapper>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>
        </:documentation_panel>

        <:props_panel>
          <.custom_search class="mb-16" />
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg lg:text-2xl font-bold">Form Wrapper Component Props</h2>

            <.custom_table id="form-wrapper-props">
              <:header>
                <.table_th>Name</.table_th>

                <.table_th>Type</.table_th>

                <.table_th>Required</.table_th>

                <.table_th>Description</.table_th>
              </:header>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>id</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>A unique identifier used to manage state and interaction.</.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>class</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>Custom CSS class for additional styling.</.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>variant</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>
                  Determines the style of the form. Supported values: <strong>default</strong>, <strong>outline</strong>, <strong>transparent</strong>, <strong>shadow</strong>, <strong>bordered</strong>.
                </.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>color</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>
                  Determines the color theme of the form. Supported values: <strong>natural</strong>, <strong>primary</strong>, <strong>secondary</strong>, <strong>success</strong>, <strong>warning</strong>, <strong>danger</strong>, <strong>info</strong>, <strong>silver</strong>, <strong>misc</strong>, <strong>dawn</strong>. Default is <strong>natural</strong>.The
                  <strong>default</strong>
                  and <strong>bordered</strong>
                  variants have extra color options: <strong>dark</strong>
                  and <strong>white</strong>, which in both light mode and dark mode, these colors are always the same.
                </.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>border</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>Determines the border style.</.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>rounded</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>Determines the border radius.</.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>padding</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>Determines padding for items within the form.</.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>space</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>Determines space between items.</.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>size</.table_td>

                <.table_td>string</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>
                  Determines the overall size of the elements, including padding and font size.
                </.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>for</.table_td>

                <.table_td>any</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>The data structure for the form.</.table_td>
              </:row>

              <:row>
                <.table_td>as</.table_td>

                <.table_td>any</.table_td>

                <.table_td>No</.table_td>

                <.table_td>The server-side parameter to collect all input under.</.table_td>
              </:row>
            </.custom_table>
          </div>
        </:props_panel>

        <:cli_panel>
          <.custom_cli_props config={component_config()} />
        </:cli_panel>
        <.custom_table_content>
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#overview"} title="Overview of Form Component" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#base-forms"} title="Base Variant" />
          <:content
            link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#outline-variant-forms"}
            title="Outline Variant"
          />
          <:content
            link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#default-variant-forms"}
            title="Default Variant"
          />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#shadow-variant-forms"} title="Shadow Variant" />
          <:content
            link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#bordered-variant-forms"}
            title="bordered Variant"
          />
          <:content
            link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#transparent-variant-forms"}
            title="Transparent Variant"
          />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-rounded"} title="Rounded prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-border"} title="Border prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-size"} title="Size prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-space"} title="Space prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-ring"} title="Ring prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-floating"} title="Floating prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-error_icon"} title="Error icon prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-label-prop"} title="Label prop" />
          <:content
            link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-description-prop"}
            title="Description prop"
          />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-name-prop"} title="Name prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-value-prop"} title="Value prop" />
          <:content link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-errors-prop"} title="Errors prop" />
          <:content
            link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-start-end-section-slot"}
            title="Start and End Section Slots"
          />
          <:content
            link={~p"/chelekom/docs/forms/#form-form-wrapper"}
            title="Form wrapper component"
          />
        </.custom_table_content>
      </.custom_tab>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layouts.app>
